President Obama has announced his intent to nominate several individuals for key administration posts. David J. Berteau is nominated for Assistant Secretary of Defense for Logistics and Materiel Readiness. Leigh A. Bradley is nominated for General Counsel at the Department of Veterans Affairs. Mona Dixon is nominated for a position on the Board of Directors of the Corporation for National and Community Service. Mark Scarano is nominated for Federal Cochairperson of the Northern Border Regional Commission. President Obama also intends to appoint Jeffrey Bleich as a member of the J. William Fulbright Foreign Scholarship Board, Michael K. Goto as United States Commissioner for the Commission for the Conservation and Management of Highly Migratory Fish Stocks in the Western and Central Pacific Ocean, Mary Lou Leary as Deputy Director for State, Local, and Tribal Affairs at the Office of National Drug Control Policy, August William "Bill" Ritter as Representative of the United States for the Western Interstate Nuclear Board, and William Sabol as Director of the Bureau of Justice Statistics at the Department of Justice. President Obama praised the nominees and appointees for their experience and dedication to their roles.